cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR

The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for image recognition in the domain of Ground Penetration Radar (GPR) data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes an improved CNN model, which suggests the possibility of it falling under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of AI techniques for automatic detection of rebar also suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the impact of different rebar arrangements and window sizes on the accuracy of results, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
